‚ùì Review Questions & Answers
Q1: Why make displayInfo() a pure virtual function?
A: To enforce that all derived classes must provide their own implementation, ensuring polymorphic behavior and making LibraryItem an abstract base class.

Q2: What's the purpose of the static member totalItems?
A: It maintains a class-level counter that tracks how many library item objects exist in the entire system, shared across all instances.

Q3: Why declare the destructor as virtual?
A: When we delete objects through base class pointers, the virtual destructor ensures that both base and derived class destructors are called, preventing memory leaks.

